Installing eGFRD
----------------
$ git clone https://github.com/ecell/epdp.git
$ cd epdp
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/root
$ make -j4

Runtime for Michaelis-Menten reaction
-------------------------------------
The reaction model is a modified version of the benchmark Michaelis-Menten 
model provided in Supporting Information Text S1 of Andrews et al, PLoS Comp 
Biol 2010.

1. To run the reaction with eGFRD:
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp PYTHONPATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp LOGLEVEL=FATAL python reaction.py 

2. To run the reaction using small molecule radius with eGFRD:
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp PYTHONPATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp LOGLEVEL=FATAL python reaction_small_r.py 

3. To plot and view the results:
   $ python ../plot_reaction.py

Runtime for diffusion
---------------------
1. To run single instance of the diffusion benchmark model:
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp PYTHONPATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp LOGLEVEL=FATAL python run_single.py

2. To run all instances of the diffusion benchmark model:
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp PYTHONPATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp LOGLEVEL=FATAL python run_all.py

3. To run all instances of the diffusion benchmark model with high concentration
   diffusing molecules:
   $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp PYTHONPATH=$HOME/wrk/epdp LOGLEVEL=FATAL python run_all_dense.py

4. To view the plot after running the models:
   $ python ../plot_diffusion.py

